text: Gotta find the entry for this slip.
Theodora Youmans must be the owner!
Take a look!

Hi! *cough* Can you help- *cough cough* Can you help me- *COUGH COUGH COUGH* Um, are you okay? Oh, I'm fine! Just a little hoarse. Ha! What do you call a pony with a sore throat? Huh? A little horse! Ha! You're funny. I got that one from my Gramps! Can you help me? I need to find the owner of this slip. Well, I can't show our log books to just anybody. Please? It's for Grampa Leo. He's a historian! Leo... you mean Leopold? Your gramps is awesome! Always full of stories. Yup, that's him! Guess it couldn't hurt to let you take a look. Here's the log book.
Do you know who Theodora Youmans is? Hmmm... not sure. Why don't you try the library? Unless you're too busy horsing around. Ha! Good one. Thanks for the help!
Nice seeing you, Jolie!
I should find out if she can help me!
I should check that logbook to see who owned this slip...

Jolie! Where have you been? Wells got in trouble for littering at the Wildlife Center. PLEASE tell me you're doing better than he is. I'm doing great! I figured out the flag! Good. Let's hear it. I'm glad I put you on the case. Thanks! Looks like your work here is done. I'll see you tomorrow at the exhibit! Are you going home now? Tomorrow's the big day! Gramps and I are going to the park by my house. I want to run around and play! Isn't that Governor Nelson Park? Huh? You know, the guy who started Earth Day! He got a park named after him? Cool!
That doesn't prove your case.
It's an ecology flag! Hmm. What does that symbol have to do with ecology?

It's a theta symbol, which also looks like the letters \"e\" and \"o\" combined. The \"e\" stands for \"ecology\" and the \"o\" stands for \"organism\"! Fascinating! Do you know how our flag was used?
That doesn't prove your case.
Governor Nelson gave a speech in front of our flag on the very first Earth Day! How exciting! Governor Nelson helped launch a huge conservation movement! Did you find any photos for the exhibit?
That doesn't prove your case.

Here are some photos of activists marching on the Capitol. They're carrying home-made ecology flags! Nice work, Jolie! Those are the real Wisconsin Wonders... Ordinary people standing up for what they believe in!
Jolie! I was hoping you'd stop by. Any news on the flag artifact? I haven't quite figured it out just yet... Well, get on it. I'm counting on you to figure this out!
I'm not sure that's relevant here...
That doesn't prove your case.
Was Wells right? Is the symbol a deer hoof?
That doesn't prove your case.
I checked at the Wildlife Center. It's not a deer hoof! Hmmm. Then what is our flag?

Our next artifact is this spectacular women's suffrage tunic! This shirt belonged to Theodora Youmans... I still say taxidermy would've been better. Admit it, you think Teddy's cute. Sure, for a weasel. *sigh* Hey, I almost forgot. The boss has one more badge for you! Ooh! What badge? History Detective. She wants you to keep helping out around here. YES!!! I'm gonna need an office, and a flashlight, and night vision goggles... Don't get carried away. Ha! Carried away? I'm just getting started. Jo Wilder is on the case!
null
null
null
She helped get votes for women!
Where are you Theodora?
Hey! That's Governor Nelson in front of our flag!
The libarian said I could find some information on Youmans in here...
Did you drop something, Dear?
Wells! What was he doing here? I should ask the librarian.

Welcome back, Dear! How can I help you? I need to learn more about this flag! It has something to do with ecology. Hmm... those stripes remind me of the American flag. Your flag must have been part of a national movement! Go check the microfiche. Maybe you'll find something!

Oh, hello there! You look like you're on a mission. Two missions, actually! Have you seen a badger around here? I'm afraid not. Please let me know if you do. It's important! I'm also looking for Theodora Youmans. Have you heard of her? Theodora Youmans? Of course! Check out our microfiche. It's right through that door.
Did you drop something, Dear? There's a card on the floor.
It's such a nice fall day.
Weren't you going to check out our microfiche? I'm sure you'll find Theodora in there somewhere!
Where should I go again? You could try the archivist. Maybe he can help you find Wells!
Check out the archives. They've got tons of old photos!

I found the flag! Governor Nelson used it on the first Earth Day! Wow! You figured it out! Now I just need some old photos, like last time. The boss is gonna love it!!! You could try the archives. Though the archivist might be too busy to help... Oh, trust me. He'll make time.

What was Wells doing here? He was looking for a taxidermist. What's a taxidermist? Not sure. Here, let me look it up. Oh my! \"Taxidermy: the art of preparing, stuffing, and mounting the skins of animals.\" Oh no... Teddy! I need to find Wells right away!! Do you know where he is? You could ask the archivist. He knows everybody!
There are some old newspapers loaded up in the microfiche.
I should ask the librarian where to go next.
I should ask the librarian why Wells was here.
Our shirt is too old to be a basketball jersey! I need to get to the Capitol and tell Gramps!
The slip is from 1916 but the team didn't start until 1974!
Anything useful on here?
Gramps said to look for clues. Better look around.
Maybe I should take a closer look at that plaque...
Ooh... \Ecology flag by Ron Cobb.\
If I were you, I'd go to the library and do some digging.
There should be some info about that symbol in my book.

Hey, nice dog! What breed is he? Actually, he's a badger. Oh, cool! I've never seen a badger in real life. You've got a million flags here! Yep. I'm a vexillophile! A vexy-wha? It just means flag expert. How can I help? I'm investigating this flag. Can you take a look? Hey, I've seen that symbol before! Check it out!
It's an ecology flag! Do you know what this flag was used for? I'm not sure. If I were you, I'd go to the library and do some digging. Good idea. Thanks!
That hoofprint doesn't match the flag!
Ugh... I think that lynx is looking at me funny.

Gah. I can't believe this. I'm a historian, not a zookeeper! And this place is dirty, and itchy, and- I love it! Of course you do. You've got a rodent following you around. Actually, badgers aren't rodents- Whatever.
My friend is a flag expert. She should be able to help you out.

So? What'd you find out? Looks like it's not a deer hoof. Great. Just great. Could this day get any worse?! Hey, Wells... I think I can help with your animal problem. Ha! I don't need your help. Fine. Then I guess you don't want a real, live badger for the exhibit. Wait! What?! Really? Wells, meet Teddy. 😊 He says he'd be willing to help out. Yes!!! I'm saved! A real, live ferret! He's. A. Badger. And we still need to figure out that flag! Fine, fine. Let's see... Actually, I went to school with somebody who LOVES old flags. Why don't you go talk to her? I'll let her know you're coming.
What is it, Teddy? Oh no... they got sick from polluted water? Poor foxes!

Oh no! What happened to that crane? Her beak is stuck in a coffee cup. It's lucky we found her. Ugh! Those cups are all over the place. I need to get her free. She won't hold still! Can Teddy and I help? Sure! Give it a try. Careful. That beak is sharp! We need to calm her down, Teddy. Any ideas? 🧘 Yoga does sound nice. But cranes can't do yoga, Teddy! 🍩 Cranes don't eat donuts! Besides, you just ate my last snack. 🦗 Oh yeah, cranes eat insects! Luckily there are tons of insects around here... Got one! Maybe she'll let me take off the cup!
Thanks for your help, kid!
You did it! Thanks, kid. Can I help you with anything? I'm investigating this symbol. Does it look like a deer hoof? There's a diagram of animal tracks over there. Go take a look!
People sure drink a lot of coffee around here.
It's OK, girl! Look, I found you a cricket!

Ooh, nice decorations! Thanks. Did you figure out the shirt? Yes! AND I know who took Teddy! Who on earth is Teddy? And where's your grampa? Here I am! Sorry for the delay, Boss. There was a bit of a... situation... in my office. Wells sabotaged Gramps! AND he stole Teddy!!! One step at a time, Jo. Did you figure out the shirt? I knew you could do it, Jo! Now can I tell you about Teddy?? We need to save him! Whew. You won't BELIEVE the day I've had! YOU! Huh? YOU STOLE TEDDY! I did no such thing! Wait- who's Teddy? Don't play dumb! Easy, Jo. Why don't you prove your case? Keep your chin up, Jo. We'll find Teddy! Nice work on the shirt, Jolie! Leopold, can you run back to the museum? The next artifact should've arrived by now. Sure thing, Boss! Jo, meet me back at my office. I hope you find your skunk, or whatever.
null

The archivist saw Wells at Bean Town this morning! I DID get coffee, but that doesn't mean I stole your badger! You just said the archivist was at Bean Town, too. I stop at Bean Town every morning. But... there's more!
That doesn't prove your case.
Alright. Teddy is my pet badger. He was napping in Gramps's office... And someone kidnapped him! How do you know he was kidnapped?
That doesn't prove your case.
I found a coffee cup from Bean Town! And Gramps only drinks Holdgers! That's true. How does a coffee cup prove Wells took Teddy?

Wells was looking for a taxidermist! HE WANTS TO KILL TEDDY! Actually... I asked Wells to find a taxidermist. I want to have animals at the exhibit! I'd prefer live animals. But we need a back-up plan. Wha... but... Then who took Teddy??? No idea, kid. But it wasn't me.
That doesn't prove your case.
That doesn't prove your case.
Yes! I solved it! So? What's the story? Well, remember that slip? What slip?
That doesn't prove your case.
That doesn't prove your case.
Head back to the museum. Your gramps is waiting for you.
Okay. What did you find out? It's a dry cleaning receipt! How do you know?
That doesn't prove your case.
That doesn't prove your case.
Wow! That's her! So Youmans wore this shirt in women's rights marches! What a fantastic piece of history- and what impeccable research!

I found his scarf! Teddy would NEVER leave without his scarf! Alright, everybody hold up- Are you telling me there's a LIVE badger in MY museum? WE'LL DEAL WITH THAT LATER, MRS. M. Watch it, Jo. Did you find any other clues?
That doesn't prove your case.
Jolie! I was hoping you'd stop by. Any news on the shirt artifact? I haven't quite figured it out just yet... Well, get on it. I'm counting on you and your gramps to figure this out!
The shirt belonged to Theodora Youmans! Hmm. I've heard that name before. Who is Theodora Youmans? I had the same question. So I went to the library to get some answers.

Of course! Youmans was a suffragist! Yep! She fought to get women the right to vote. Very good, Jolie! The fight for women's suffrage is an important part of Wisconsin history. But where does the shirt come in?
That doesn't prove your case.
That doesn't prove your case.
An expert opinion. Good thinking! Where did you go from there? Well, I had to figure out WHICH cleaner the receipt was from. How did you narrow it down?
That is definitely no slip...

You found the right cleaner on the first try? What a lucky break! Gramps always says I'm his good luck charm! What did you do at the cleaner's? I wanted to find out who owned the shirt- So I checked the logbook.

Look at that! It's the bee's knees! Can we hurry up, Gramps? Teddy and I were gonna go climb that huge tree out back! Hmmm. Don't forget about your homework. Your teacher said you missed 7 assignments in a row! Well, I did SOME of those. I just couldn't find them! Did you do all of them? No... because history is boring! I suppose historians are boring, too? No way, Gramps. You're the best! Then do it for me! Your teacher said you could help me for extra credit. Go ahead, take a peek at the shirt!
I'll record this in my notebook.
Guess I should look for clues.

Find anything? Just this old slip from 1916. Hot Dog! I knew it! I'm not so sure that this is a basketball jersey. Wait, you mean Wells is wrong?! Could be. But we need evidence! Why don't you head to the Basketball Center and rustle up some clues? Ooh, I like clues! I'll be at the Capitol. Let me know if you find anything!
Um... what did you want me to do again? Head over to the Basketball Center. Hopefully you can rustle up some clues!
Have a look at the artifact!
I need to find more info about Theodora!
I should go to the Capitol and tell Mrs. M!
I should go to the Capitol and tell Mrs. M!
I should go to the Capitol and tell Mrs. M!
I should go to the Capitol and tell everyone!
I need more context about how the flag was used.
Better check back later.
The archivist said I should look in the stacks.

Teddy! I'm sure glad to see you. The archivist had him locked up! Gadzooks! Poor critter. You're becoming quite the detective, Jo. Notice any clues about this flag? Well... it looks hand-stitched. Aha! Good catch, Jo. Go on, tell the boss what you found!
Why don't you go talk to the boss? She's right outside.

I'm telling you, Boss. Taxidermy is the way to go! Nonsense. I want live animals at the exhibit, not stuffed ones. Ah, Jolie! I'm glad you're here. I'm putting you in charge of the flag case. Make sure to get some old photos for the exhibit, like last time! Wait! Can't I do it? The symbol on the flag looks sort of like a deer hoof. It could be an early design for the Wisconsin state flag! Wells, you already have a job to do. Jolie, you can look into this deer hoof theory.

Let's get started. The Wisconsin Wonders exhibit opens tomorrow! Who wants to investigate the shirt artifact? Well, Leopold here is always losing papers... Hey! It's true, they do keep going missing lately. Ha. Told you so! Besides, I already figured out the shirt. It's a women's basketball jersey! That settles it. Wells, finish up your report. Leopold, why don't you help me set up in the Capitol? We need to talk about that missing paperwork. Will do, Boss. Hey Jo, let's take a look at the shirt!
The archivist must've taken Teddy!
What now, kid? Do you really think that symbol is a deer hoof? Not sure. Do I look like a deer expert to you?
Why don't you go play with your grampa?
Come on, kid. You're slowing me down.
null

Do you know where I can find a deer expert? Hmm. You could try the Aldo Leopold Wildlife Center. Ugh. I have to head over there and check out the animals. I'll ride with you! FINE. That possum better not scratch my leather seats... He's a badger!
Your grampa is waiting for you in the collection room.
Head over to the Wildlife Center! I'm sure they'll be able to help.
I should see what Gramps is up to!
I should go talk to Gramps!
I should see what Grampa is up to!
Gramps must be up in the collection room. Let's go find him!
Jo! Check out the next artifact! What is it? I think it's a flag! Pretty spiffy, eh? I don't have time for this, Gramps. Teddy is still missing! We'll find him, Jo. Want to look for more clues?

Hey, look at those scratches! The kidnapper probably took Teddy on the elevator! Great Scott, you’re right! Why isn't the button working? We'll need a key card. I had one, but Teddy chewed it up. I’ve got Wells’s ID! Let's follow those scratch marks! Jo! I can't go with you. I need to take the artifact upstairs. It's okay, Gramps. I'll go by myself. Teddy, here I come!
We'll find Teddy. We just have to keep our eyes open!
I'll be in the collection room. Come find me when you're ready to check out the artifact. Good luck!
This button never works!

Hey! What are you doing down here? GRRRRRRR GAH! And what is THAT doing out of its cage?! You stole Teddy! How could you?! What's going on here? Thanks for coming, Boss. I told you! I captured a badger in our museum! He's been eating my lunch every day this week! No he hasn't! 😐 Teddy! Did you really eat his lunch? 😐 Did you steal Gramps's paperwork too?! 😐 And my homework?!?! 😐 See?! That thing's a monster! I don't have time for this. Jolie- keep your badger under control, or he'll have to go. YEAH! And you, Frank- YEAH! Wait- me? You can't just steal Jolie's pet. Don't you know badgers are protected animals? Besides, he looks friendly to me. Wha?! Ugh. Fine. 😝 Alright, Jolie. Back to work. Your grampa is waiting for you in the collection room. Come on, Teddy. Let's go find Gramps!
I found the key! ❤️ Come on, let's get out of here! Here's your scarf back!
Whoever lost these glasses probably took Teddy! How can I find out whose glasses these are? Oh! There was a staff directory in the entryway! I'll go look at everyone's pictures!
I wonder whose glasses these are.
Teddy!!! 😭 Hang on. I’ll get you out of there!
I should check out that pair of glasses.
It’s locked!
Can't believe I lost my reading glasses.
I need your help! *grumble grumble* And you are? I'm Leopold's grandkid! I don't have time for kids. Now if only I could read this thing. Blasted tiny letters...

Ah, that's better! Did you have a question? Yes! I was wondering- Wait a minute! Where did you get that coffee? Oh, that's from Bean Town. I ran into Wells there this morning. Wells? I knew it! Knew what? Did you have a question or not? Yes! Do you know anything about this slip? I found it on an old shirt. An old shirt? Try the university. You can talk to a textile expert there. What's a textile expert? They study clothes and fabric. Great! Thanks for the help!
I used to have a magnifying glass around here…
You're still here? I'm trying to work! Run along to the university. You can talk to a textile expert there.
What are you waiting for? The Stacks are right outside the door.

I need to find Wells!!! Calm down, kid. I haven't seen him. I can't calm down. This is important! Sorry, can't help you. Ugh. Fine. Do you have any info on Theodora Youmans? Theodora Youmans? Is that who owned the shirt? Yep. Why didn't you say so? Youmans was a suffragist here in Wisconsin. She led marches and helped women get the right to vote! Wait a sec. Women couldn't vote?! Nope. But Youmans and other suffragists worked hard to change that. Thanks to them, Wisconsin was the first state to approve votes for women! Wow! Here's a call number to find more info in the Stacks. Where are the Stacks? Right outside the door.
I found it! Theodora wearing the shirt! You better get to the capitol!

You again! Don't let him hurt me! 🙄 Actually, we're just here for some photos. It's for the flag display! Wait a minute... YOU'RE the new history detective everybody's talking about? Guess so! YOU?! Teddy's helping too. What kind of photos do you need? Something to do with ecology and Wisconsin. Here's a call number for the Stacks. Go find some photos. Just please, don't let your badger eat them!
The Stacks are right outside the door. Go find some photos!
I bet the archivist could use this!
I don't need that right now.
Yes! It's the key for Teddy's cage!
Is this your coffee, Gramps? Nope, that's from Bean Town. I only drink Holdgers!
Teddy's scarf! Somebody must've taken him! Try not to panic, Jo. Maybe he just got scared and ran off. But he never goes anywhere without his scarf! I think he's in trouble!
What the- What happened here?! I don't know! I got here and the whole place was ransacked!
I should help Gramps clean. Maybe there's a clue in this mess!
Poor Gramps! I should make sure he's okay.
What should I do first? Head upstairs and talk to the archivist. He might be able to help!
So much cleaning to do...

Who could've done this? I have an idea. He's wrong about old shirts and his name rhymes with \"smells\"... Hold your horses, Jo. BUT WELLS STOLE TEDDY! Could be. But we need evidence. Fine. Let's investigate! I'm afraid my papers have gone missing in this mess. You'll have to get started without me. Don't worry, Gramps. I'll find Teddy! And I'll figure out the shirt, too. I knew I could count on you, Jo! Why don't you go upstairs and see the archivist? He's our expert record keeper.
Can you help me tidy up?
I love these photos of me and Teddy.
Found it!
Gramps is the best historian ever!
Whatcha doing over there, Jo? Just talking to Teddy. I gotta run to my meeting! Meetings are BORING! Grab your notebook and come upstairs!
Hang tight, Teddy. I'll hurry back and then we can go exploring! Now where did I put my notebook? 😴
I love these photos of me and Teddy!
I feel like I'm forgetting something.
Come on, Jo! Meet me back in my office and we'll get started!
null
That doesn't prove your case.
Ah, yes! The basketball jersey. IT'S NOT A JERSEY! How do you know?
That doesn't prove your case.

Jolie! What are you doing here? The shirt is not a basketball jersey! Aha! Did you find something? What are you talking about? Gramps had me look for clues about the artifact. WELLS WAS WRONG AND GRAMPS WAS RIGHT!!! Hold on. Which artifact?
I found this slip on the shirt. It's from 1916! How does that prove our shirt is not a jersey?
I found this slip on the shirt. It's from 1916! Our shirt was around WAYYY before the women's basketball team!
I checked the Basketball Center. The women's team didn't start until 1974! How does that prove our shirt is not a jersey?
I checked the Basketball Center. The women's team didn't start until 1974! Our shirt was around WAYYY before the women's basketball team!
That doesn't prove your case.
Well? What are you still doing here? Go find your grampa and get to work!
I don't think we have anything like THAT in the collections...

Wow! I think you're right, Jolie. Leopold, I need you to work on this right away. Yippee! How 'bout it, Jo? Want to help me investigate? Not really... Let me know when you figure it out. In the meantime, I need to have a word with Wells.
Which place might know about the slip?
This place was around in 1916! I can start there!
You haven't seen any badgers around here, have you? Badgers? No. But I hear the museum's got one on the loose! Yeah. Thanks anyway.

Hello there! Wow! What is all this stuff? It's our Norwegian Craft exhibit! Can I give you the tour? Sorry, I'm in a hurry. Do you know what this slip is? Looks like a dry cleaning receipt. Ooh, thanks! Now I just need to find all the cleaners from wayyyy back in 1916. Yikes... this could take a while. Maybe I can help! I've got a stack of business cards from my favorite cleaners. Why don't you take a look?
I should stay and look for clues!
I wonder if there's a clue in those business cards...

Wow! The Capitol looks so pretty from here! Neat, isn't it? That's where it all happens. Wisconsin folks come together at the Capitol to make their voices heard. Like they did with Earth Day! You know, there's a nice little Earth Day display down the path. Go check it out! Aren't you coming too? Oh, you go ahead. I'll stay here and watch the sunset.

Wow! Governor Nelson was just a normal guy from Wisconsin... And he changed the world! We should have a march, Teddy. No more plastic cups!!! 💚 Maybe they'll even name a park after us! Except our park will have roller coasters, and cute animals, and snacks. Make sure to get plenty of rest tonight, Teddy. We've got work to do!
You and Teddy go check out the Earth Day display. I'll stay here with the sunset.
Ugh! Somebody needs to do something about all these cups!
